hands_on_practices.solution:
Relevant equation:
$$D_A(R)=R\bigl(1-\tfrac{2M}{R}\bigr)^{-1/2}.$$
Differentiate with respect to $R$:
$$\frac{dD_A}{dR}
=\bigl(1-\tfrac{2M}{R}\bigr)^{-1/2}
+R\bigl(-\tfrac12\bigr)\bigl(1-\tfrac{2M}{R}\bigr)^{-3/2}
\frac{d}{dR}\bigl(1-\tfrac{2M}{R}\bigr).$$
Compute the inner derivative:
$$\frac{d}{dR}\bigl(1-\tfrac{2M}{R}\bigr)=\frac{2M}{R^2}.$$
Thus
$$\frac{dD_A}{dR}
=(1-\tfrac{2M}{R})^{-1/2}
-\frac{M}{R}(1-\tfrac{2M}{R})^{-3/2}.$$
Setting $dD_A/dR=0$ gives
$$(1-\tfrac{2M}{R})^{-1/2}
=\frac{M}{R}(1-\tfrac{2M}{R})^{-3/2}.$$
so
$$1-\frac{2M}{R}=\frac{M}{R}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
1=\frac{3M}{R}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
R=3M.$$
